{ Finesse in the ending For a description of Flohr’s skill in this game, I
commend you to Roget’s Thesaurus, where you will find such adjectives as
exquisite, elegant, artistic, and enchanting. Throughout the play there are delightful finesses and touches of originality. Who but Salo Flohr would
interrupt a series of exchanges, force an irreparable weakness, and then proceed to complete the exchanges? To my mind, this quiet little positional game, played with cry stalline clarity, outshines all the blazing combinations of a dozen wide-open, slam-bang attacking games. }
