make a fine support for the Knight when it arrives at c4. Meanwhile, the
square b7 is made avail able to the Queen, who will strengthen the attack on White’s center. } { [%csl Gf6][%cal Gf6d7,Gd7b6,Gb6c4,Yc7b7] } 16. Rad1 Rc8 { Increases the pressure on the c-file. } 17. a3 Qb7 { Threatens the life of the e-Pawn. } { [%csl Re4] } 18. Qd3 Nd7! { Two possibilities are now open to the
Knight: (1) To attack the e-Pawn once more by 19 … ♘c5, forcing White to
give up his good Bishop for the Knight, and, (2) To swing the Knight over to the outpost c4, by way of b6. } { [%csl Re4][%cal Gd7c5,Yd7b6,Yb6c4] } 19. b4 { Eliminates the first possibility } 19... Nb6 { But not the second! } 20. Bc1 (20. Nd5 Bxd5 21. exd5 Na4! { the threats of winning the exchange by 21 … ♘b2, or of
