starboard side } { [%cal Gc8a6] } 18. Be3! { An excellent move! It prevents the advance of Black’s
c-Pawn, while two more black squares (d4 and c5) come under White’s
domination. } { [%csl Rc5,Rd4] } 18... Ba6 19. Kd2! { The King is a strong piece and should be used aggressively in the ending.
As the number of pieces on the board diminishes, so is the danger lessened
