for further entry by the King. } { [%csl Rg6][%cal Gd4e5] } 29... Rg8 { The Pawn must be protected, and this is of course preferable to 29 … ♖h6,
and the Rook has no mobility to speak of. } (29... Rh6 { [%csl Rh6] }) 30. Ke5 { Further penetration along the convenient black squares. The threat is now
31 ♔f6 (attack the g-Pawn twice) 31 … ♗e8 32 ♖e1 (stronger than 32 ♔xe6)
followed by ♖xe6. } 30... Be8 { Black’s poor Bishop is sadly shut in by the five Pawns standing on the
