{ The Galloping Knight One piece wins this game practically single-handed!
Tarrasch’s Queen Knight makes 13 of the 37 moves in the game, holds the
enemy Rooks at bay, captures Pawns here and there, and as a final touch, clears the way for a passed Pawn to become a Queen. From the technical
standpoint, the game offers a valuable lesson in the art of getting the most out of a minute advantage. Especially interesting is the way the Knight provokes a weakness which enables it to gain complete possession of d6 - a square the Knight visits three times! }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d6 { The authorities do not recommend this line, the Steinitz defense, since
