of it, his King being nearer the center for the endgame. } 16... e6 17. Rhc1 Bf8 18. Rxc8 Rxc8 19. Rc1 Rxc1 20. Bxc1 Bd6 { This is rather lifeless } (20... b4 { would have made things more difficult for Pillsbury. } { [%cal Ga7a5] }) 21. Bd2 Kf8 22. Bb4 Ke7 23. Bc5! a6 (23... a5 { if only to prevent White from giving his strongly-placed
Bishop additional support by 24 b4. } { [%cal Rb2b4] } 24. b4 axb4 25. Bxb4 Bxb4 26. Nxb4 Kd6 27. g4 f6 { [%cal Ge6e5] }) 24. b4 f6 25. g4 Bxc5 { Gunsberg becomes impatient, pro bably considering the position an easy
