{ Quiet, Like a Tiger One of America’s leading players once said to me that
he liked games where nothing happens. This one of Botvinnik’s, I am sure,
would please him. There are little combina tions in the game, but they appear only in the notes. Botvinnik wins the game purely by strength of
position. Control of the d-file, with emphasis on the key square d5, enables his pieces to penetrate the adverse position. The exchanges which take place about the 30th move clear off some of the heavy pieces, and leave Botvinnik a Pawn ahead in a Rook and Pawn ending. He wins it in a breeze. }
