Attack - lively and with vigor, (this is the dominant theme of the movement, and determines the play of the entire composi tion). (2) The Knight’s Tour - lightly and gracefully. (3) The Rook’s Maneuvers - with energy and spirit. (4) The Pawn Finale - simply and precisely. You may get the idea from
